In [[differential geometry]] and [[mathematical physics]] (especially [[string theory]]), the '''Polyakov formula''' expresses the [[conformal geometry|conformal]] [[calculus of variation|variation]] of the [[Minakshisundaram–Pleijel zeta function|zeta functional determinant]] of a [[Riemannian manifold]]. The corresponding density is local, and therefore is a Riemannian curvature invariant. In particular, whereas the functional determinant itself is prohibitively difficult to work with in general, its conformal variation can be written down explicitly.
