'''Victor Borisovich Lidskii''' ({{lang-ru|Виктор Борисович Лидский}}, 4 May 1924, [[Odessa]] – 29 July 2008, [[Moscow]]) was a [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] and [[Ukraine|Ukrainian]] [[mathematician]] who worked in [[spectral theory]], [[operator theory]], and [[plate theory|shell theory]]. Lidskii discovered the [[Trace_class#Lidskii.27s_theorem|Lidskii theorem]] in 1959. His adviser at [[Moscow State University]] was [[Israel Gelfand]].
